body:
- $fwrite ignored during _for_ loop in an _initial_ statement
- Occurs on `Verilator 5.021 devel rev v5.020-68-gd6f8ccd` also seen on v5.018

```
module test;

integer f,cnt;

initial begin
	f=$fopen("zeros","wb");
	for(cnt=0;cnt<1024;cnt=cnt+4)
		$fwrite(f,"%u",32'd0);
	$fclose(f);
end

endmodule
```

This will create a 1024-byte long file using *iverilog*, but results in a 0-byte file with *verilator*

[test files](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/14072983/verilator_fwrite.zip)
